We have seen several instances become completely unresponsive since the June release. We can't SSH in to them and need to get Contegix to force a reboot. Contegix reported this:

{quote}
Just a heads up that one of the support leads has raised this issue to my attention. Since the upgrades have completed, over the past 24 hours we've seen somewhere in the neighborhood of a dozen studio instances exhaust all available virtual memory on the system, mandating a forced reboot of the VM to restore service.  This doesn't include those that Matt Jensen and I experienced several times while performing the upgrades.

At this time, we don't have the entire list of those dozen available, but just a couple noted on that issue.  We will be gathering as much information as possible on any future events when they occur.  Just wanted to give you guys the preemptive heads-up in case this becomes a bigger issue in the over the next 24-48 hours.
{quote}

